@mohitsharma0690 : Thanks for the report. However, could you please add some more detail, for example, a minimal set of steps one can take to reproduce the problem? For example, I tried the following on my OS X El Capitan laptop (where I use virtualenv):

virtualenv --system-site-packages ~/tf-venv
source ~/tf-venv/bin/activate 
export TF_BINARY_URL=https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/mac/cpu/tensorflow-0.11.0rc1-py2-none-any.whl
pip install --upgrade $TF_BINARY_URL
python -c "import tensorflow; print tensorflow.__version__"

and got the following output (no errors):

python -c "import tensorflow; print tensorflow.__version__"
